18/04/2004
MITROVICA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Two US female police officers died in Mitrovica Saturday (17 April) when a Jordanian, also serving with the UN force, opened fire on their vehicle as they left a local detention centre after completing a training course there. 
The perpetrator was also killed in the ensuing shootout. 
A UN spokesman denied initial reports that the victims and their killer had had an argument shortly before the incident. 
Neeraj Singh said there had been no contact between the two parties. 
UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri issued a statement expressing shock and dismay over the shooting. 
He sent condolences to the families of the victims and their government. 
(The New York Times - 18/04/04; AP, Reuters, AFP, BBC, CNN - 17/04/04)
